Class Processing

  • java.lang.Object
    • logic.Processing

  • public class Processing
extends java.lang.Object
    Processing class manages all computational logic for the Certified Tester Calculator This class acts as a controller in a MVC - fashion

      • appendDigit

        public boolean appendDigit(java.lang.String in)
        Appends a String that represents a single digit to the numberline, if possible
        Rules for failure:
        1) Length of Numberline is greater than MAXDIGITS(21)
        2) Numline == "0" and "0" is entered. 3) If length of in is greater than 1
        Parameters:
        in - Digit to append Numberline
        Returns:
        true - String appended, false - nothing changed

      • appendDot

        public boolean appendDot()
        Appends a Dot to the Numberline, if possible
        Rules for failure:
        1) Length of Numberline is greater than MAXDIGITS(21)
        2) Last "digit" is a dot. No Multiple dots! Digit to append Numberline
        Returns:
        true - dot appended, false - nothing changed

      • clear

        public void clear()

      • backspace

        public void backspace()
        Performs a backspace operation on the Numberline. This will delete the last character on the numberline. If the numberline is empty after this operation, the numberline will be set to "0".

      • sqrt

        public boolean sqrt()
        Parses the numberline, calculates the square root of this number. The result will be stored in the storage and displayed in the numberline. A squreroot sign with the radicand will be displayed in the equationline. fails when:
        radicand less than 0
        Returns:
        true - Update GUI. false - no update necessary

      • pow

        public boolean pow()
        Parses the numberline and multiplies it by it self. The result will be set to the numberline and stored in the storage. The equationline will display the input with a power of 2 sign. In addition the numberline will display the result of the operation.
        Returns:
        GUI update - false, no update is necessary.

      • operation

        public void operation(char op)
        this function will set the operator for a binary operation. In addition it will parse the current value in the numberline and stores it in the storage. The operation will be displayed in the equationline and the numberline will be set to "0".
        Parameters:
        op - operation as Char - allowed operations: +, -, *, /, s (square), r (square root)

      • equal

        public boolean equal()
        Loads the stored value and parses the numberline to 2 operators of a binary operation. The operation will be determine by operatrion stored with the operation - method. The Result is saved in the storage and set to the numberline. In addition the full expression will be set to the equationline. Binary operations are: +, -, *, /
        fails when:
        1) no values was stored
        2) unsupported operation is used
        Returns:
        success
